<subSubSection id="C3466511FFC6FFFA75D1AEA8C408AA73" pageId="5" pageNumber="511" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE3369AFFC6FFFA75D1AEA8C595A928" blockId="5.[151,1437,1189,1828]" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFC6FFFA75D1AEA8C731A8E4" bold="true" box="[151,348,1189,1215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Diagnosis. Male.</emphasis>
Postcranium black with gray pruinescence; thorax and abdomen shiny black, legs predominantly yellow (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA75B2AEC4C73DA8B8" box="[244,336,1225,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); distal section of vein M 
<subScript id="17D834DFFFC6FFFA772AAED1C419A8B1" attach="left" box="[620,628,1244,1258]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">4</subScript>
longer than vein dm-m (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA76CFAEC4C58DA8B8" box="[905,992,1225,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); male tergite 8 acute distally (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA7071AEC4C3E2A8B8" box="[1335,1423,1225,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
); epandrium with posterodorsal lobe somewhat thin and higher than anterodorsal lobe (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA7115AEE0C2C2A95C" box="[1107,1199,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); anterior cercus narrow, with distinct falciform mesial process (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA77C6AF1CC4BEA970" box="[640,723,1297,1323]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
); cercal bridge small, subtriangular (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA7124AF1CC2D8A970" box="[1122,1205,1297,1323]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
); median cercus well elevated with distinct setae (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA748DAF38C44DA914" box="[459,544,1333,1359]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
); posterior cercus with three branches distally (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA7167AF38C2FBA90B" box="[1057,1174,1333,1360]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Figs 4E, F</figureCitation>
); ventral process of cercus inconspicuous; hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA74B9AF54C439A928" box="[511,596,1369,1395]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
) with few posterior setae at basal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE3369AFFC6FFFA7581AF70C2E4AA58" blockId="5.[151,1437,1189,1828]" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFC6FFFA7581AF70C773A9CC" bold="true" box="[199,286,1405,1431]" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA7468AF70C713A9CC" box="[302,382,1405,1431]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4I</figureCitation>
). Without pinnate scales on hind tibia; wing approximately as wide as male wing, rather hyaline; tergite 8 elongate, wider at base, with distal sinus (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA7651AFACC504A9E0" box="[791,873,1441,1467]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4J</figureCitation>
); sternite 8 higher laterally on posterior third and ventrally with two less sclerotized spots at distal one quarter (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA7617AFC8C5A7A9BB" box="[849,970,1477,1504]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Figs 4J, K</figureCitation>
); genital fork well sclerotized, slightly Tshaped (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA75B2AFE4C726AA58" box="[244,331,1513,1539]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4L</figureCitation>
), with genital chamber membranous with small sclerotized area (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC6FFFA7163AFE4C210AA58" box="[1061,1149,1513,1539]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,181,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[155,1432,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus melanothorax Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2009. Holotype ♂ (A–H).A. Habitus, lateral view (apex of abdomen detached); B. Wing; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Epandrium detached, lateral view; E. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; F. Cerci lobes, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterodorsal view; G. Cerci lobes, dorsal view; H. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (I–L) from Brazil. I. Habitus, lateral view; J. Tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view; K. Sternite 8, ventral view; L. Genital fork and genital chamber, dorsal view (Figs J–L after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009)). Scale bars, figures A, I = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C, H, J–K = 0.2 mm; D–G, L = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: a ce, anterior cercus; c brd, cercal bridge; m ce, median cercus; mpac, mesial process of anterior cercus; p ce, posterior cercus; sbepand scl, subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921359/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE3369AFFC6FFFA7581AC00C408AA73" blockId="5.[151,1437,1189,1828]" box="[199,613,1549,1576]" pageId="5" pageNumber="511">
